---
layout: base.njk
title: Template Evidence Ledger | OpenAgreements
description: Per-template validation status, source provenance, and field metadata.
---

<main class="main-wrap">
  <section class="section" style="padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) clamp(16px, 4vw, 48px);">
    <h1>Template Evidence Ledger</h1>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: 640px; margin: 8px 0 4px;">
      Validation status for every template in the catalog.
      Each row shows source provenance, licensing, and whether the template has
      dedicated automated tests.
    </p>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 0 0 24px;">
      Generated {{ templateEvidence.generated_at_utc | truncate(19, true, "") }} UTC
      &middot;
      <strong>{{ templateEvidence.validated_count }}</strong> validated,
      <strong>{{ templateEvidence.not_covered_count }}</strong> not covered,
      <strong>{{ templateEvidence.not_applicable_count }}</strong> n/a
      &middot;
      {{ templateEvidence.total_templates }} templates total
    </p>

    <div style="overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;">
      <table class="evidence-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Template</th>
            <th>Source</th>
            <th>License</th>
            <th>Fields</th>
            <th>Validation</th>
            <th>Last Run</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for t in templateEvidence.templates %}
          <tr>
            <td>
              <strong>{{ t.displayName }}</strong>
              <br><code style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--ink-soft);">{{ t.id }}</code>
            </td>
            <td>
              <a href="{{ t.sourceUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="color: var(--accent-deep); text-decoration: none;">{{ t.sourceLabel }}</a>
            </td>
            <td>
              {% if t.license == "Recipe" %}
                <span class="template-license recipe">Recipe</span>
              {% else %}
                <span class="template-license">{{ t.license }}</span>
              {% endif %}
            </td>
            <td>{{ t.requiredFields }}/{{ t.totalFields }}</td>
            <td>
              {% if t.validation_status == "validated" %}
                <span class="status-validated">Validated</span>
              {% elif t.validation_status == "not_covered" %}
                <span class="status-not-covered">Not covered</span>
              {% else %}
                <span class="status-not-applicable">&mdash;</span>
              {% endif %}
            </td>
            <td>
              {% if t.last_validation_at %}
                {{ t.last_validation_at | truncate(19, true, "") }}
              {% else %}
                &mdash;
              {% endif %}
            </td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 32px; padding: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); background: var(--bg); font-size: 0.88rem;">
      <h3 style="margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 0.95rem;">About validation status</h3>
      <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; color: var(--ink-soft);">
        <li><strong class="status-validated">Validated</strong> &mdash; template has dedicated Allure test(s) that exercise the fill pipeline with template-specific payloads.</li>
        <li><strong class="status-not-covered">Not covered</strong> &mdash; template exists in the catalog but has no dedicated validation test yet. General fill-pipeline tests still exercise the template engine.</li>
        <li><strong class="status-not-applicable">N/A</strong> &mdash; recipe template downloaded at runtime from upstream source; not pre-validated in the test suite.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p style="margin-top: 20px;">
      <a href="/trust/" style="color: var(--accent-deep);">&larr; Back to Trust</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</main>
